  "text": "The atypical degenerative dementias are an unusual collection of disease processes that are typically more aggressive than the disorders discussed in part 1 [CITATION_1] . The initial clinical presentation of atypical degenerative dementias can often be confusing, and both prognostication and symptomatic management can be greatly aided by accurate diagnosis with the help of anatomic and metabolic imaging (Table 1) .",
